metadata.title: Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil
aws::graph::propositions: # Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil Variants and Designations
Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil is powered by a derated Arriel 1D1 engine.
The derated Arriel 1D1 engine improves the Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil helicopters' life cycle.
Eurocopter Squirrel HT.1 is a designation of AS350BB.
Eurocopter Squirrel HT.1 was formally operated by the British Military.
Eurocopter Squirrel HT.1 was operated through the Defence Helicopter Flying School.
Eurocopter Squirrel HT.1 was used as a training helicopter.
Eurocopter Squirrel HT.2 is a designation of AS350BB.
Eurocopter Squirrel HT.2 was formally operated by the British Army Air Corps.
Eurocopter Squirrel HT.2 was used as a training helicopter.
Eurocopter Squirrel HT.2 was based at Middle Wallop.
Eurocopter Squirrel HT.2 is now retired.
AS350 C is an initial variant of Lycoming LTS-101-600A2 powered version.
AS350 C was developed for the North American market.
AS350 C was marketed as the AStar.
AS350 C was quickly superseded by AS350D.
AS350 D is powered by one Lycoming LTS-101 engine.
AS350 D was developed for the North American market.
AS350 D was marketed as the AStar.
AS350 D was at one stage marketed as AStar 'Mark III.'

text:
Powered by a derated Arriel 1D1 engine to improve the helicopters' life cycle.
Eurocopter Squirrel HT.1
Designation of AS350BB formally operated by the British Military, through the Defence Helicopter Flying School as a training helicopter.
Eurocopter Squirrel HT.2
Designation of AS350BB formally operated by the British Army Air Corps as a training helicopter, based at Middle Wallop. Now retired.
AS350 C
Initial variant of Lycoming LTS-101-600A2 powered version developed for the North American market as the AStar.  Quickly superseded by AS350D.
AS350 D
Powered by one Lycoming LTS-101 engine for the North American market as the AStar.  At one stage marketed as AStar 'Mark III.'
